Moreover, the enhanced electron-hole Coulomb interactions in valley-characteristic TMD-ML’s also give rise to efficient inter-valley excitonic couplings that, via the intrinsic e-h exchange interaction, intermix the spin-allowed exciton states of distinct valleys69,75,76,92. Figure 1a depicts the e-h exchange interaction that couples an intra-valley exciton carrying the momentum ℏQ in the K-valley to that in the K′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
